                            <comment id="14713373" author="shalinmangar" created="Wed, 26 Aug 2015 13:14:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk move to 5.4 after 5.3 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14721530" author="upayavira" created="Sun, 30 Aug 2015 14:14:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have noted these issues with exceptions in the angular UI:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;it doesn&apos;t handle core init failure display&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;it displays the full JSON, not just the message&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;when an exception shows, it doesn&apos;t ever clear unless you reload the entire page&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14721561" author="upayavira" created="Sun, 30 Aug 2015 15:16:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Handles core initialisation issues (both on page load, and within core admin tab)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Displays just the message for the exception&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Keeps a list of known exceptions, and clears them when an AJAX call is made for the same endpoint&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;If this patch behaves as expected, I&apos;d like to think exception handling is done, and the angular UI has reached a stable enough state to go into active service.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
